# Architecture: Agentic Code Review Assistant

## Guiding Principles

1. **Dependency Rule**: dependencies point inward only вЂ” outer layers depend on inner layers, never the reverse. Domain is the innermost core; Application wraps it; **API** and **Infrastructure** are sibling outer layers (both depend inward). Runtime request flow: `API в†’ Application в†’ Domain (interface) в†’ Infrastructure в†’ external systems`
2. **Interface isolation**: all external systems (DB, GitHub, AI, Redis) are accessed through interfaces defined in Domain; Infrastructure provides the implementations
3. **No framework bleed**: Domain and Application layers have zero imports from FastAPI, SQLAlchemy, or any third-party library
4. **Async-first**: every I/O operation is `async`; no blocking calls in the request path
5. **Single responsibility per agent**: each LangGraph agent node has one concern; SynthesisAgent owns reconciliation

