## Backend вЂ” Key Architectural Rules

### Dependency Injection (container.py)
All use case instances are built once in `container.py` and injected via FastAPI `Depends()`.
No use case instantiates its own dependencies вЂ” all deps are constructor-injected interfaces.
See `backend-standards.mdc` for code examples.

### Error Hierarchy
```
DomainError           в†ђ base for all domain rule violations
ApplicationError      в†ђ use case / orchestration failures
InfrastructureError   в†ђ wrapped external system errors (DB, API, queue)
```
API layer `error_handler.py` maps these to HTTP status codes.

### Agent State (LangGraph)
`ReviewState` (TypedDict in `infrastructure/ai/graph/state.py`) is the single shared object flowing
through the graph: `pr_metadata`, `diff_chunks`, `context_chunks` (RAG), `active_agents`
(set by Supervisor), `findings` (accumulated), `synthesis` (final output).

### Async Webhook Pattern
`POST /webhooks/github` в†’ validate HMAC в†’ enqueue to Redis в†’ return `202`.
Worker: `queue.pop()` в†’ `RunReviewPipelineUseCase` в†’ LangGraph в†’ post GitHub comments.

