## Review Package Assembly

Before any agent runs, the worker assembles a structured **Review Package** from the raw
PR data. This is done in `RunReviewPipelineUseCase` and stored in `ReviewState`.

### Structure

```
ReviewPackage
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ pr_metadata
в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ title, description, author
в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ base_sha, head_sha, base_branch, head_branch
в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ changed_files: list[{path, status: added|modified|deleted, additions, deletions}]
в”‚
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ context_units: list[ContextUnit]       в†ђ one per function/class containing в‰Ґ1 changed line
в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ file_path
в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ node_type: "function" | "class" | "module"
в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ node_name
в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ start_line, end_line
в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ body_old: str                      в†ђ complete old version (from base_sha)
в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ body_new: str                      в†ђ complete new version (from head_sha)
в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ diff_patch: str                    в†ђ unified diff for this unit only
в”‚
в””в”Ђв”Ђ rag_chunks: dict[AgentType, list[CodeChunk]]   в†ђ populated per-agent before its run
    в”њв”Ђв”Ђ security в†’ top-5 auth/crypto/input-handling functions
    в”њв”Ђв”Ђ perf     в†’ top-5 DB/loop/IO functions
    в”њв”Ђв”Ђ arch     в†’ top-5 import/class-hierarchy chunks
    в””в”Ђв”Ђ test     в†’ top-5 test files related to changed modules
```

### Assembly Pipeline

```
1. Fetch raw diff from GitHub (base_sha в†’ head_sha)
2. For each changed file:
   a. Fetch new file content (head_sha)
   b. Fetch old file content (base_sha) вЂ” skip for added files
   c. Parse both with tree-sitter в†’ extract function/class nodes
   d. Identify which nodes contain в‰Ґ1 changed line (by line range intersection)
   e. Build ContextUnit: body_old, body_new, diff_patch for that node
3. Embed all new file content в†’ store in code_embeddings (if not already for this SHA)
4. SupervisorAgent reads context_units metadata (file types, node names) в†’ decides active agents
5. Before each specialist agent runs в†’ query pgvector with agent-specific query в†’ populate rag_chunks
```

### Large Function Handling

Functions >300 lines are trimmed to preserve the context budget:
```
signature + first 30 lines
...
[N changed lines В± 10 lines of surrounding context]
...
last 5 lines before return statement
```

### Large PR Handling (>50 changed files)

Split context_units into batches of 10 files. Each agent is called once per batch.
SynthesisAgent receives all batch findings and deduplicates across batches.

### Embedding Cleanup

On `pull_request.closed` webhook:
```sql
DELETE FROM code_embeddings
WHERE repository_id = $repo_id AND commit_sha = $head_sha
```
Weekly background cleanup removes rows older than 30 days as a safety net.
